Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getMsvMode(25.10)                                            getMsvMode(25.10)

Name
       getMsvMode  -  Gets the special handling for inter-domain nets and uses
       effective power domains for ISO/LS insertion

Syntax
        getMsvMode

       [-help]

       [-allowNestedDefaultDomain]

       [-allowPowerDomainMinGapZero]

       [-checkAllNetsForDomainCrossing]

       [-handleBackToBackIsolation]

       [-handlePD {true|false}]

       [-handlePDComplex {true|false}]

       [-honorCpfGlobalConnectionSpecForAoBuffer]

       [-honorCpfGlobalConnectionSpecForShifter]

       [-honorDotLibRelatedPGPin]

       [-honorEffectiveDomainForIsoLsInsertion]

       [-markIsoEnablePinAsAlwaysOn]

       [-notUseTopFTermDomainForVoltage]

       [-nonDefault]

       [-shareWellAOBufferingSupport]

       [-upf_allow_shifter_voltage_mismatch]

       [-upf_insert_on_floating_pins]

       [-quiet]

       Gets the special handling for  inter-domain  nets  and  uses  effective
       power domains for ISO/LS insertion. For more details see setMsvMode.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getMvsMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getMvsMode.

       parameter_names
              Returns  information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

       -quiet Displays the current settings in Tcl list format only.

Related Information
              * setMsvMode

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

